title: Fu Fish
overview:
Fu Fish
    
        Play Fu Fish demo game online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. No download required.
about_game: It’s like shooting fish in a barrel… well, in the ocean at least. Fu Fish is an unusual slot with an undersea theme and no reels. You have to dive in to see the issues with its nominally high RTP.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Fu Fish is an almost wholly unique form of slot machine. In place of a spin button, the player has a cannon. Instead of aiming to land winning combinations, the player uses that cannon to shoot fish and is paid a certain amount when the fish explodes.
The player competes with other players, who have their own cannons, and the constant risk of missing, of kill poaching, and of course of shooting expensive rounds at cheap fish.
The idea of shooting fish is certainly a novel one for a slot theme, but it is the execution that really makes this game stand out.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The visuals are this slot's main appeal. A dozen different fish, turtles, whales, dragons, flotsam and jetsam move across the screen in endless groups and shoals.
Everything is animated, from the cannon shots to the exploding fish, from the languid swim of a shark to the frenetic writhing of the dragons. The animations are all unique, clear, and well formed. Though the screen can get pretty busy with tens of fish swimming and up to six players firing tracer rounds into the water.
The sound effects are a little repetitive, the cannon fire is ongoing as is an annoying steel band loop that is supposed to evoke the Caribbean but mostly just irks the player.

media.caption: Gameplay of the Fu Fish slot

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay for Fu Fish is unusual but simple. The player has a gun they aim with their mouse (or finger in the touchscreen version). The goal is to shoot the fish that swim past, winning prizes for the fish you kill. Every shot costs the player one bet (the bet size is set by a slider).
Every fish has a cash prize, the harder they are to kill the bigger the prize. The prizes are valued in multiples of bets.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are no Wilds or Free Spins in Fu Fish, thanks to its unusual gameplay style.
The closest things to bonuses are the dragons and golden sharks which have randomised high payouts (between 50x and 500x the bet for the sharks, between 200x and 888x for the dragons).
There are also special objects like the mines which clear the screen of fish, paying out for all those fish to the player who detonated the mine. Some fish come with multipliers of their own.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is potentially as high as 97.00%, but the unusual gameplay makes the exact amount somewhat dependent on the player. The number of 97% only works if the player wastes zero shots. Wasting shots is easy as tough fish will often swim away before they take enough rounds to die, and other fish can swim in front of targets.
For comparison, our yardstick for average is roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site ran from $/£/€0.01 per shot up to $/£/€10.00 per shot. Given the rapid fire of the cannon in this game, those bets can rack up fast, making this game one in which players should take extra care with their bankroll management.
The publisher has not released any data on the volatility of this game, which makes recommending the slot difficult. Especially since sticking to high volatility slots is one of the cornerstones of our slot strategies. However, on the basis of how the game pays out it seems likely that the volatility is relatively low for this slot.

media.caption: High paying fish in the Fu Fish slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Fu Fish stands in a category of its own thanks to its unusual game mechanics. That uniqueness is a definite draw as is the high theoretical RTP.
However, in practice the RTP is unlikely to be that high as there are a lot of ways in which the game generates wasted bets.
While this game does not meet the standards set by our preferred slot strategies, the gameplay may well be interesting enough to lure a few players in.

title: Cai Shen Ye
overview:
Cai Shen Ye
    
        Play Cai Shen Ye demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Join Cai Shen Ye for a simple, beautiful slot experience with an RTP of 97.31% and high volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Cai Shen Ye, one of the gods of wealth most associated with gambling, is evoked in the title of this slot but less so on the reels. The beautifully rendered imagery is more generically Chinese: fish kites and holed coins make up a background to the reels, on which each symbol is a disk, which has been drawn to look almost like traditional jade carvings.
It is really more style than theme but it works for this slot.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are pretty flawless. There is a sense of class about almost every aspect of this slot, from the circular symbol designs to the small but clear animations that highlight winning combos. Everything has an effortlessness about it.
The "almost" in "almost every aspect" must be stressed, because the music is a nightmarishly upbeat loop that can’t be more than a few bars long and will drive the sturdiest of players insane in no time at all.

media.caption: Win in the Cai Shen Ye slot

Gameplay.text:
Cai Shen Ye is a perfect example of simplicity done right. It is a five reel slot machine with three rows per reel.
The any way wins system means that players simply count symbols in adjacent reels starting from reel one and going leftwards without worrying about win lines.
An additional nice touch is that each symbol on the fifth reel (also called the Money Shot reel) has a numerical value on it. If a player hits five of a kind, then the win is for the coin value multiplied by that symbol's numerical value.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol and appears only on the middle three reels.
Three or four Scatter symbols in one spin will trigger the Free Spin bonus. The player is awarded either nine free spins for three Scatters or twenty-seven free spins for four.
During the free spin bonus, the middle reel is held still and consists of three Wild symbols.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is a whopping 97.31%. This is well over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.50 up to a maximum of $/£/€250.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is very high, which makes it an awesome slot to use with our slot machine strategies.

media.caption: Paytable of the Cai Shen Ye slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Cai Shen Ye is an immensely popular slot, and for good reason. The simple but beautiful visuals complement solid gameplay and excellent design.
When you add to this the fact that the RTP is well above average and the volatility is perfect for our preferred slot strategies, you can see why we give this game our full recommendation.

title: Hot Shot Progressive
overview:
Hot Shot Progressive
    
        Play Hot Shot Progressive demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Save yourself some time and don’t give Hot Shot Progressive a shot. The game has one interesting gimmick and a whole stack of negatives to weigh against that.

Theme and Storyline.text: Hot Shot Progressive is an attempt to take the classic fruit machine design and gussy it up for the modern five reel slot world. If this strikes you as a wholly redundant exercise, you are already one step ahead of Microgaming’s marketing department who green-lit this boring theme without the one feature that makes it stand out i.e. old school simplicity.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The mistakes on Hot Shot Progressive are immediately obvious on the surface level. The graphics are at best bland and at worst tacky.
The reel animations for this slot are agonisingly slow, and without a fast spin button, you are forced to sit through the whole animation which is both dull and long. Then if you win you are subject to a second round of unskippable and interminable visuals.
On top of this, the sound effects are bizarrely poor. Each one appears to have been cut off a fraction of a second before it finishes and none of the noises work together. It is a cacophony of electronic gibberish.

media.alt: Hot Shot Progressive bonus game win
media.caption: Bonus game win in Hot Shot Progressive slot machine

Gameplay.text:
Gameplay in the base game is the only place there is a spark of joy in the whole rotten mess. There is the usual five by three format and 40 winlines, but in place of bonus games there are a series of Scatter symbols (see below for details), a different kind for each reel.
This gives the game a little bit of sorely needed individuality.

media.alt: Hot Shot Progressive base game paytable
media.caption: Base game paytable
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are no Wilds in Hot Shot Progressive slot. However, there are a variety of Scatters.
Each reel has a special Scatter symbol that lands with a three-by-three reel slot machine within the symbol. If three or more Scatters land, this triggers one spin on each of these mini slot machines.
With the exception of the Diamond 7s bonus, all the Scatter slots have a single win line.
Reel one’s Scatter slot is called Blazing Sevens and is a basic spin and win game.
Reel two has the Diamond line slot which is the same, but has three win lines instead of one.

media.alt: Hot Shot Progressive - Double 7 jackpot paytable
media.caption: Paytable for Double 7 jackpot

media.alt: Hot Shot Progressive - Diamond Line scatter paytable
media.caption: Paytable for Diamond Line scatter

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.04%. This is neither good nor bad when measured against the yardstick we use for the industry.
The range of bets on the site we tested was oddly narrow with a minimum bet per spin of  $/£/€0.40, which is a little high for the lowest rollers out there. The maximum, on the other hand, was $/£/€24.00 per spin, which will leave any high rollers out there feeling frustrated. While the majority of middle stakes players will be happy, this game does exclude those on the edges of the bell curve.
The volatility of this game is at the low end of medium. This is a little too low to work well with our slot machine strategies.

Conclusion.text:
Hot Shot Progressive is a terrible slot. Ugly to look at, horrible to play and without a high enough return to player or volatility to make up for its many downsides.
It has one redeeming feature in its innovative game-within-a-game Scatters, but you're far better looking elsewhere for your slot related needs.

title: Wild Ape
overview:
Wild Ape
    
        Play Wild Ape demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: This average RTP, high volatility, jungle-themed slot is filled with mysterious primates and entertaining bonus features.

Theme and Style.text:
Wild Ape takes players on a journey deep into a jungle.
In the sweltering heat, players will wander among palm trees and encounter wild animals. If they are fortunate, a mysterious gorilla may show them hidden treasures.
This slot is a good fit for those looking for an exotic escape.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The soundtrack of Wild Ape uses a dramatic drumbeat to create tension. Flute notes and animal calls help create an immersive jungle atmosphere.
The reels are crafted from golden bamboo stalks and in the background, players will glimpse a lush landscape of palms, waterfalls, and vines. Dappled sunlight suggests a thick canopy of leaves overhead, reinforcing the natural setting.
Among the symbols, players will find letters animated in rich jewel tones that bring to mind tropical fruit. Jungle wildlife such as adorable lemurs, majestic toucans, and fierce crocodiles also make an appearance.
However, the titular character of the reels is a dignified gorilla who looks out from the reels with a confrontational expression. His face is illuminated by golden sunlight as he meets the player’s gaze, clearly ready to defend his jungle home.
Overall, the soundtrack and animation of this slot create a moody jungle world.

Gameplay.text:
Wild Ape is a five-reel, three-row slot, with 20 win lines available during the base game. The number of win lines increases to 40 during special features.
All winnings are paid from left to right and only the highest win per line is awarded.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Bonus symbol.
The Bonus symbol appears on reels 1, 3, and 5 and triggers the appearance of the Bonus wheel. Players will be prompted to spin the Bonus wheel to be awarded as many as 20 free spins and up to 50 added Wild symbols.
If players land 3 consecutive stacks of Ape symbols, the Wild Ape Respins feature will begin. During this feature, all of the Ape symbols will become Wild and players are granted 3 respins.
During both the Wild Ape Respins feature and the Free Spins feature, the number of win lines increases from 20 to 40.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.01%, almost exactly our yardstick for an average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€20.00 per spin.
Since Wild Ape has high volatility, this slot is a good match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Pursuing the highest possible volatility is our suggested strategy for selecting slots.

Conclusion.text:
We recommend this average RTP, high volatility, jungle-themed slot.
Mathematically-minded players will like Wild Ape’s combination of a decent RTP and ample volatility.
Meanwhile, the range of bonuses and the vivid animation ensure that this slot remains engaging.

title: Dead or Alive 2
overview:
Dead or Alive 2
    
        Play Dead or Alive 2 demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: The West is given a melancholy paint job in this dark but popular Pekinpah-esque take on the Western with great graphics, high volatility and an RTP of 96.80%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Dead or Alive 2 is a slick Western themed slot from NetEnt. The game casts the player as a no good bounty hunter looking to reap the rewards of finding, and bringing in, the villains of a small fictional town in 1800s America. Pony up and you’ll be hunting varmints in no time, bringing them in either dead or alive.
The set up is good, the world well built, and the characters varied. The game manages to build its quite wide ranging character roster using clever gameplay variations, symbols and bonuses.
If you’ve never played at being a cowboy before, now’s your chance.

media.alt: Dead or Alive 2 top paying symbol win
media.caption: 4 of a kind win with top paying symbol

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The game benefits massively from some well thought through visual features.
Small details in the animation, like the way the bottles hanging from the reels sway on their strings when the player spins the reels, make the game feel immersive and alive despite the abandoned desert town that makes up the backdrop.
The reel and win animations are also perfectly blended with the sound and the music to make the whole game feel integrated and responsive. Coupled with the charming and varied characters that make up the symbols along with the miscellaneous artefacts of Western life, this makes for a game that is both recognisably part of the Western genre, and distinct from other similarly themed slots.

Gameplay.text:
The base game is played on five reels with three rows, and nine win lines.
There is no gamble feature, but Dead or Alive 2 makes up for that with multiple bonus games.
What features it does have are all given a nice lift by musical stings, animations, and gameplay twists that keep the player engaged and pace the game out beautifully.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. There are five different Wild symbols but the differences are purely visual.
Two or more Scatter symbols anywhere on the reels result in a payout. Two symbols get the player twice their bet per spin, while five nets 2,500 times their bet per spin.
Three or more Scatter symbols will also trigger one of three Bonus games. Each Bonus starts with twelve free spins. The type of bonus is selected at random.
During Old Saloon Free Spins, all wins are multiplied by two. If at least one Sticky Wild lands on every reel during a spin, five additional spins are added to the total number of spins.
During High Noon Free Spins, when multiple Wilds land on the same reel, they transform into a multiplier wild – x2 for two Wilds on the same reel and x3 if there are three. If at least one Sticky Wild lands on every reel during a spin, five additional spins are also added to the total in this Bonus too.
During Train Heist Free Spins, a counter is added to the reels. This records the current multiplier, which increases by one whenever a Wild symbol lands on the reels. When a Wild lands, an additional free spin is also added to the total. If the counter reaches x16, then another five additional free spins are added to the total number of free spins.

media.caption: Each reel has distinctive Wild symbol

media.alt: Dead or Alive 2 choose your bonus game
media.caption: Pick one of three bonus games with 12 free spins each

media.alt: Dead or Alive 2 Train Heist free spins
media.caption: Train Heist bonus game has the lowest volatility

media.alt: High Noon Saloon free spins & Sticky Wilds
media.caption: Sticky Wilds & multipliers plus highest volatility - that's High Noon Saloon bonus game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.80%, well over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.09 up to a maximum of $/£/€9.00 per spin. The high bet here is strangely low, and your mileage may differ on other sites.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it a perfect match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Especially when coupled with the nice return to player.

media.alt: Dead or Alive 2 high symbols paytable
media.caption: Top symbol's paytable

Conclusion.text:
Dead or Alive 2 is hugely popular and with good reason.
It has a lot of visual flare and atmosphere, generating a bleak dog eat dog world in a parched desert town.
On top of that, NetEnt have built a slot with high volatility, an RTP of 96.80%, and the kind of quality gameplay mechanics you would expect from a studio that have been in this business for so long.
We highly recommend this slot.

title: Narcos
overview:
Narcos
    
        Play Narcos demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Cops and drug runners play cat and mouse in this high concept, medium-high volatility slot with an RTP of 96.23%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Narcos is a licenced slot machine adaptation of the popular Netflix series about the head of the Medellin cartel, Pablo Escobar, and the law enforcement officials who eventually caught and killed him.
It is an exciting world rendered in rich detail by the artwork which mirrors modern comic books in their digital painting style.
Although the actual likenesses of the actors are rather loosely rendered, they are close enough to be recognisable and the slot does a good job of capturing the tone of the show. So if you’re a fan or just enjoy a cross between neo-noir and neo-western, dive on in.

media.caption: Mega win in the Narcos slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are one of the strongest features of the Narcos slot. The artwork is perfect, capturing the warm South American feel in the colour palette of a spaghetti Western. The symbols are detailed without being busy and each of them has their own animation when they are part of a win.
The other animations are also varied and theme-driven. Each feature uses different borders, colours and animations to make them distinct from each other, while the sound effects match up to the movements perfectly.
The whole deal is then tied together with a nicely cinematic and grown-up version of a mariachi band on the soundtrack.

media.caption: Drive-by random feature appears in the base game

Gameplay.text:
Narcos is a five reel by three row slot, with an any way wins system. This means symbols need only to appear on consecutive reels starting with reel one to form a win. This results in 243 ways to win.
There are also several features of gameplay that are triggered randomly in the base game. For example, the Drive By Feature changes some of the high-value symbols into Wilds.
Couple this with the walking wilds and bonus games (details below) and you have exciting gameplay that is as varied and exciting as the lives of drug smugglers and the cops who hunt them.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol and the Locked Up symbol.
A Walking Wild can appear at random during any spin and will remain on the reels, moving one space to the left with each spin, adding a little bit of variety to the everyday spins.
Scatter symbols only appear on reels one, three and five. One Scatter on each of those reels give the player ten Free Spins.
The big winnings come from the Locked Up symbol though.
When three or more of these land anywhere on the same row, they are moved together and assigned a random value between one and ten times the player’s bet per spin.
The player then gets three Locked Up Spins. During Locked Up Spins the symbols are either blank, Locked Up Symbols, or Golden symbols. Any non-blank symbols that land lock in place and when a group of three symbols forms, or a new symbol lands next to a group, then the spin number resets to three. Golden symbols add either larger values or can increase the value of symbols already in a group.
At the end of the last spin the value of all symbols in a group are added up and the amount paid out to the player.

media.caption: Walking Wild feature win

media.alt: Narcos slot Locked up bonus feature
media.caption: Best paying bonus of the game - Locked Up feature

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.23%, a little over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€400.00 per spin. This kind of spread easily covers most players.
The volatility of this game is on the cusp between medium and high. As a result, this slot is a pretty good match for our preferred slot machine strategies, which target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable for Narcos slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Narcos is a beautiful game with a pitch perfect ear and eye for setting the tone and style of the TV show from which it borrows its name. By itself, the slot’s design could have sold us on this slot.
The RTP (96.23%) and volatility (medium-high) are also in the zones that we like and would match well with our slot strategies.
In fact, we have very little to narc on when it comes to this slot. We give Narcos a wholehearted recommendation.

title: Sirens Treasures
overview:
Sirens Treasures
    
        Play Sirens Treasures demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: The siren’s song may have lured plenty of sailors to their ruin, but Siren’s Treasures does not.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The sirens of Homeric legend were half-bird, half-woman and sang with such intoxicating voices that men would wreck themselves on the rocks about their islands following their musical lure.
However, anyone bold enough to brave this slot’s various rocky waters might come away with some portion of their treasure. If they aren’t wrecked upon the rocks, that is.
On the reels, sunken chests and amphoras live alongside still floating triremes and alluring sirens. While an excellent theme for a slot, its execution leaves a lot to be desired.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The music is probably this slots strongest feature, a rousing movie style soundtrack with ghostly choral undertones designed to imitate the song of the sirens.
The rest of the game’s front end is much weaker, the background is a pretty typical looking seascape while the reels are messy and uninterestingly designed. No care seems to have been given to generating a unified feel for this slot. It seems like each individual aspect of the visuals and animations was designed in a hermetically sealed room.

Gameplay.text:
The base game is a pretty standard five by three slot with fifty winlines.
Some effort has been made to spice up this formula by adding a Mystery symbol which adds nothing to the gameplay except for delays, by hiding a few identical symbols and revealing them to be all identical.
More usefully there are win multiplier symbols that apply a multiplier of between two and five to any wins on that spin. There are also basic Free Spin and Bonus games (details below). All in all, Siren’s Treasures tries and magnificently fails to be anything more than the most standard of slots.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Free Spin and Bonus symbols. The Wild symbols are frequently stacked. If three Wilds land to fill up one whole reel, then wins are calculated, the Wilds locked in place, and a re-spin takes place.
Three or more Bonus symbols anywhere on the reels will trigger the Bonus game. This is a simple picking game where you turn over icons to reveal prizes.
Three or more Free Spin symbols anywhere on the reels will trigger the Free Spin feature with 10 free spin.
During Free Spins, a three times multiplier is applied to all wins and Wild’s are sticky. When a sticky Wild lands on the reel, it remains in place for all future free spins.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
Spinomenal does not provide the return to player information for this slot. This is a real red flag for us, as the absence of this information could be covering for an extortionate vigorish.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.50 up to a maximum of $/£/€500.00 per spin. This tips the balance heavily towards those with some serious coin to spend.
The volatility of Siren’s Treasures is medium, which makes it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies that favour highly volatile slots.

Conclusion.text:
Like most of Spinomenal’s offerings, Siren’s Treasures disappoints at almost every level. Their slots come with routinely low returns to the player, and this slot is no exception. Couple this with the lazy design and low volatility and this slot is easily dismissed.
On top of this we noted frequent server issues with the Spinomenal slots we tested, which were not present on other slots. Your mileage may vary.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Where the first two Demi Gods slots riffed on the Ancient Greek pantheon, Demi Gods III looks further north for its inspiration to the equally popular realm of the Norse gods.
In place of Zeus and his Olympian crew, Demi Gods III offers up renderings of Odin, Frigg, Thor, Loki and Tyr to fill out reels rich with references to Norse myth and decorated with the flare that Spinomenal excel at when they pull their thumbs out.
The Norse gods are a rich seam for the dwarven miners of the slot world to work, it is always nice to see a company give them a slot to really shine in.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
As with many of Spinomenal’s top end slots, the visuals are stunning. From gorgeous portraits of each of the gods on the reels, to the delicate silver work around the spin button, huge care has been poured into making the slot look good.
The music is suitably cinematic and lends a dramatic air to proceedings as well as being tailored to the various game modes.
The animations and sounds effects are both excellent and co-ordinated to immerse players fully in the world of Demi Gods III.

Gameplay.text:
Demi Gods III is played on five reels with three rows and fifty win lines.
The high value symbols are all made up of three symbol high portraits, effectively meaning these symbols are always stacked three high. The other symbols also tend to be stacked but can come in stacks taller than three symbols.
During the base game, multipliers of x2 or x3 can be randomly triggered.
There is no gamble feature, but Demi Gods III still provides excellent variety and pacing using its progressive series of bonuses (details below).

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Bonus symbol. Hitting five Wilds on a winline pays out three hundred times the player's bet per line.
Three or more Bonus symbols trigger the Bonus game.
The player is first taken to a map displaying the nine worlds of Norse mythology, starting with the frigid Niflheim and ending with the home of the gods: Asgard.
Each world offers a different setup and feature. For example, the first world the player unlocks (Niflheim) uses a five reel by four row setup. When the player hits a winning combination in Niflheim free spins, the winning symbols freeze in place and a respin is triggered. This continues until no new winning symbols land; at this point the winnings are calculated.
Other worlds feature Wild respins, guaranteed wins in every free spin, sticky wilds and much more. This adds a feeling of progression and variety to the game that many slots lack.

The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.50 up to a maximum of $/£/€500.00 per spin. That spread should cover all but the very smallest of stakes players.

Demi Gods III is a beautiful slot with excellent gameplay and worlds of variety in its selection of bonus games.

If the volatility doesn’t bother you, there is plenty of other stuff in this slot to appeal to players.

overview:

about_game: Take to the skies in a steampunk flying ship. Avoid storms and pirates to enjoy the 96.14% RTP and a player’s choice of volatility in free spins from low to high.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Riders of the Storm is set in a world of steampunk aviators piloting their airships through storm clouds.
They are armed with harpoons and equipped with anchors, hooks and ship’s wheels according to the charming reel artwork. Though the main tone and atmosphere comes from the billowing wine-dark clouds that roll in the background as windswept rain lashes the reels.
It’s a cool theme for a slot and one that stands out as something with potential for interesting designs.

media.alt: Riders of the Storm slot 5-of-a-kind win
media.caption: 5-of-a-kind win in the Riders of the Storm slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Unfortunately, the possibilities offered by the world of steampunk designs are in rather short supply in Riders of the Storm. The reels have three characters on them, each of which is well drawn, but the remaining symbols are simple pictures of a boathook, a wheel, and an anchor and a compass. There is not even an image of the airship that is hinted at in the opening artwork.
The soundtrack, on the other hand, is excellent. A real mid-century movie score of a piece with plenty of rain sounds mixed in.
The win and spin sounds are well chosen, feel thematic, and gel well with the neat – if very basic – animations.

Gameplay.text:
Riders of the Storm is a five reel slot. It uses an any way wins system where wins are made by sequences of symbols running left to right anywhere on adjacent reels starting with reel one.
There are three rows, which makes the win system 243 ways.
To spice things up, there is a choice of three bonus games, should the player trigger the bonus. There is also a fourth option that will randomise the bonus game.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol and come with either a two, three, or five times multiplier.
During the base game, if the Mystery Wild Reels is triggered, between one and four reels will be made into all Wilds. This happens at random in the base game only but can result in some pretty tasty wins when it does.
Three or more Scatters trigger the Bonus Game. This starts with the player choosing from four different free spin games. A low volatility option with a multiplier of x2 and 15 free spins, a medium option with 10 spins and a x3 multiplier, and the version that fits best with our preferred slots strategies – the high volatility option with just 6 spins but a multiplier of x5.
During the free spins, Wild symbols become walking Wilds, staying on the reels and moving to the left. Hitting three or more Scatters will retrigger the free spins with a randomised number of spins.

media.alt: Riders of the Storm big win
media.caption: Big win with 3 Mystery Wild Reels activated

media.alt: Riders of the Storm choices for Free spins
media.caption: Player can choose type of the Free spins bonus, that affects the volatility of the game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.14% (96.15% if the player opts for the medium volatility version), very close to our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is determined largely by the players choice of bonus. The best version for our preferred slot machine strategies is for the player to choose the highest possible volatility.

media.alt: Riders of the Storm high paying symbols paytable
media.caption: Paytable for High paying symbols of the game

Conclusion.text:
Although the theme of Riders of the Storm is a little underdeveloped in this Thunderkick's game, the slot itself is a solid piece of machinery which works well and looks pretty good.
The soundtrack is excellent and the RTP is decent. The high volatility bonus works well with our slot strategies and the mystery wheels add some ongoing excitement.
We would strongly recommend this slot.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Magic Stars is another vaguely spaced themed slot from Wazdan. Like many other Wazdan offerings, Magic Stars 6 has a kind of trippy kaleidoscopic feel, with icons made up of gem-like geometric stars and a background of hyper-colourful milky way constellations.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Lucky Reels takes the classic visuals and tone of an old one armed fruit machine and puts them in a new, modern context. The style is glossy and 3D and adds new gameplay mechanics to what was once the purview of the most minimalist machines.
Anyone who has played a few slots will know how they feel about the fruit laden reels of a game like this. If it's your sort of thing, you may wish to look a little closer at this twist on a classic.

media.caption: Big Win in Wazdan's Lucky Reels slot

The animations are simple and do the job of flagging up the action well. A speed option in the game can toggle the spin animations between slow, fast and blink-and-you’ll-miss it.
Wazdan’s stable of highly trained synth-pop composers are on hand to provide the upbeat soundtrack and seem to have been involved in the win and spin sounds which have a delightfully musical tone.
There is however a slightly off-putting male voice that comments "nice" when a multiplier falls and may make a player jump the first time they hear it.

Gameplay.text:
Lucky Reels is a six reel slot with three rows and twenty winlines.
The main feature of the base game are the multiplier symbols on the reels, which can land at any time. When they do, all subsequent spins enjoy the benefits of that multiplier until a new multiplier symbol lands and changes the multiplier to something else for the remaining spins.
There is a simple double or nothing gamble feature for players who like a little extra risk. In this game, players must predict the colour of the next card off a deck, a 50-50 proposition.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
Three or more Scatters anywhere on the reels triggers a Free Spin bonus. Three scatters win 15 free spins for the player, while four win 20, and five and six win 25 and 30 respectively.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.60%, solidly over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game can be set to low, medium, or high volatility by clicking a button in the base game. Since our preferred slot strategies target the highest possible volatility, we recommend players go with the highest level of variance in this game.

media.caption: Full paytable for Lucky Reels slot

Conclusion.text:

Wazdan’s usually excellent art department seem to have taken a lot of half days and liquid lunches while working on Beauty Fruity. Ironically - given the title - the slot looks a complete mess.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Somewhat unusual in the world of slot machines, Dr Fortuno is a fully decked out blackjack table with an orange suited Victorian style magician as the dealer. If his curly moustache and sinister smile don’t scare you off, you can play against him.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:

Overall, this game has a beautifully polished front end.

Gameplay.text:
The rules of Dr Fortuno are those of a standard six-deck blackjack game. That is to say, the show contains six decks of cards, shuffled together every hand. The player’s goal is to get closer to 21 points than the dealer without going over. If the player goes over 21, their hand loses automatically. If the player and dealer have the same number of points, the player's bet is returned in what is known as a "push".
Face cards are worth 10 points, all other cards are worth their pip value in points, except for aces which play as either 1 point or 11 points depending on which is most advantageous.
Each player receives two cards face up, the dealer receives one card face up, one face down. The players can then opt to "hit" (taking an additional card) as many times as they like, "pass" (stick with the cards they have got), or "double" (double their bet and take exactly one extra card).
If a player has two cards of the same value, they can "split", taking each card and starting a new hand with separate bets on each of them.
When the players have all gone, the dealer turns up their second card and continues to hit until their card value is over 17.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text: Because of the nature of this game, there are no Wilds, Bonuses or Free Spins.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 99.54%, provided you play perfect blackjack strategy. This is vastly higher than most slot games where two or three points on the vig is considered cheap. However, deviating from this strategy will rapidly add percentages to the house edge.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per hand of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per hand with players being able to play up to five hands at a time. This allows for an enormous turnover of bets for any high stakes players out there.
The volatility level of this game is low.

Conclusion.text:
Though sold as a slot, Dr Fortuno is really a blackjack game with some visual bells and whistles. If blackjack is your game, this is one of the more entertaining and attractive formats to play it in.
If you want something with some more reels and free spins, then you might want to give almost any other page on our site a looking over.

The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Free Spin symbol. They appear only on reels two, three and four. Wilds expand to fill the reel whenever they are going to make a winning combination by doing so.
Three or more Free Spin symbols trigger a Free Spin bonus. This consists of 8 free spins for three symbols, 12 for four and 16 for five. Three or more symbols also come with a cash pay out of x1, x10, or x100 the total bet for three, four and five symbols respectively.
During free spins, Wilds are sticky. Filling all three middle reels with Wilds triggers an additional two free spins. Extra free spins are also awarded for two or more Free Spin symbols (whereas you need at least three of them to trigger the free spins in the base game).

media.alt: Sahara Nights slot with Extra spins feature
media.caption: Player can retrigger Extra Spins during the Free Spins bonus feature

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.20%, a little over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.alt: Sahara Nights top paying symbols paytable
media.caption: Paytable for the high paying symbols

Conclusion.text:
Sahara Nights is a straightforward slot. Especially for something coming out of Yggdrasil Gaming, a company that tends to innovate with even the simplest of ideas.
But it does everything it sets out to do well. Perhaps a little too solidly, we could have used higher returns for the player and much higher volatility.
Still, taking it on its own terms it is a pretty good slot.

title: Thimbles
overview:
Thimbles
    
        Play Thimbles demo game online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. No download required.
about_game: Thimbles is a simple casino game with a low volatility, a 96% RTP, and gameplay based on a classic shell game adapted for online gambling.

Theme and Style.text:
Thimbles is a casino game that takes players into a realm of lighthearted fantasy.
Players will wander through a medievall forest until they come upon an intriguing game. With sparkling jewels on the line, players will test their skills.
Thimbles will suit players who are looking for a novel gameplay experience.

media.caption: Thimbles is a classic shell gambling game with either one or two gems

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The soundtrack of the Thimbles online casino game uses delicate string notes to evoke the mood of a medieval feast. A steady rhythm will keep players focused and immersed in the fantasy of this world.
As players enter the game, they will see three wooden buckets animated in a cartoon style. Each bucket is facing downwards, but may lean to the side to reveal what it's hiding. This allows players to confirm that a shimmering red gem is under at least one bucket.
The tantalizing buckets are placed on a dark stone background, reinforcing the rustic vibe of the setting. Surrounding the gameplay area, a sizzling green light is visible as if powerful magic is present. This adds an eerie twist to the world of Thimbles.
The settings area is animated in warm shades of brown and grey, suggesting wood and stone materials. Players will get the sense that this game is occurring in time long before our own.
Overall, the soundtrack and animation of Thimbles creates an enticing world of enchantment.

Thimbles Gameplay.text:
Thimbles is a classic "shell game" adapted for online casinos. The structure of Thimbles is a set of three buckets, under which one gem or two gems can be found.
Prior to the start of a round, players must set their desired bet level. Next, players need to decide whether they wish to play with one hidden gem or two.
After the buckets are swiftly moved around, players can select the bucket they believe is hiding a gem. If they guess incorrectly, they will lose the value of their bet. If they guess correctly when playing with one gem, they will win 2.88x their total bet. In the event that they are playing with two gems, 1.44x their total bet is awarded.
Risk is lower when playing with two gems and this is reflected in the lower multiplier.

media.caption: Lower risk - lower reward option for the Thimbles game

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins in Thimble.text:
Thimbles does not feature Wild symbols or a Free Spins feature as this would not suit the structure of the game.
Those who would prefer more conventional special features may wish to pursue different game options.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of Thimbles is 96.00%, exactly our yardstick for an average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.50 up to a maximum of $/£/€100 per spin.
Low volatility makes Thimbles a less promising match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

Conclusion.text:
We recommend this average RTP, low volatility, medievial fantasy-themed game.
Thimbles presents a novel option for players who are interested in shaking things up.
However, those with a mathematical mindset will be less allured by this game’s modest volatility.
If you wish to get to know the game before wagering real money, you can play Thimbles demo for free at the top of this page.
